Design an algorithm that solves the following problem.

A programmer wants to know which unit of data measure should be the most appropriate depending on the bytes that the user enters. The units to be reviewed are KB, MB, GB, TB and PB. Use the following reference table.



If the user enters 5045 bytes, this is divided by 1024 and the message should be 4.92 KB. 

Use this link to validate the conversion. https://discoveryformacion.com/calculadora-para-convertir-unidades-de-almacenamiento-informaticas/

Algoritmo sin_titulo
	//Ingresa los datos
	Escribir "Ingrese los bytes que desea convertir (solo bytes)"
	Leer byte
	
	//valores fijos
	kilo = 1024
	mega = 1048576
	giga = 1073741824
	tera = 1099511627776
	peta = 1125899906842624
	
	//Calculos
	Si byte < kilo
		u = " b"
		b = byte / 1
	Finsi
	
	Si byte >= kilo y byte < mega
		u = " KB"
		b = byte / kilo
	Finsi
	
	Si byte >= mega y byte < giga
		u = " MB"
		b = byte / mega
	FinSi
	
	Si byte >= giga y byte < tera
		u = " GB"
		b = byte / giga
	FinSi
	
	Si byte >= tera y byte < peta
		unidad = " TB"
		b = byte / tera
	FinSi
	
	Si byte >= peta
		u = " PB"
		b = byte / peta
	FinSi
	
	//mostrar resultados
	Escribir "La cantidad equivale a:" 
	Mostrar b , u

FinAlgoritmo

*** Ejecución Iniciada. ***
Ingrese los bytes que desea convertir (solo bytes)
> 5000
La cantidad equivale a:
4.8828125 KB
*** Ejecución Finalizada. ***


